<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">About Seedance prompt formatting</h2><div class="info-card"><p>Seedance is optimised for Chinese domestic platforms (Douyin, Bilibili) and works well with both Chinese and English prompts. It responds best to explicit, structured descriptions with clear camera movement labels.</p><p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Default ratio:</strong> 9:16</p></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Tips for Seedance prompts</h2><div class="body-copy"><ul><li>Default to 9:16 for vertical Douyin/TikTok content.</li><li>Use 'Camera:' as an explicit label before the movement description.</li><li>Specify subject positioning: 'subject in the left third'.</li><li>Add lighting direction: warm/cool, source position.</li><li>Seedance produces strong anime and cinematic style results.</li></ul></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Recommended camera moves</h2><div class="rel-strip"><span class="rel-pill">Slow Dolly In</span><span class="rel-pill">Fast Dolly In</span><span class="rel-pill">Orbit Shot</span><span class="rel-pill">Whip Pan</span><span class="rel-pill">Crane Up</span><span class="rel-pill">POV Walk</span></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Example prompts</h2><div class="prompt-list"><div class="prompt-item"><div class="pt-label">Anime action</div><div class="pt-text">A spiky-haired anime warrior sprinting through a collapsing battlefield. Camera: fast dolly rush-in, then side tracking. High-energy shonen anime. Harsh backlight, drifting embers. Fast pacing. 9:16.</div><button class="pt-copy">Copy</button></div><div class="prompt-item"><div class="pt-label">Music video</div><div class="pt-text">A vocalist under a single spotlight, smoke drifting. Camera: slow dolly push-in. Moody cinematic music video. Warm spotlight, deep shadow, haze. Steady pacing. 9:16.</div><button class="pt-copy">Copy</button></div><div class="prompt-item"><div class="pt-label">Hero orbit</div><div class="pt-text">An armoured warrior standing at the edge of a cliff. Camera: 180-degree orbit. Epic cinematic anime. Warm golden backlight, dramatic sky. Slow pacing. 9:16.</div><button class="pt-copy">Copy</button></div></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">FAQ</h2><div class="faq"><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Chinese or English for Seedance?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Both work. Chinese prompts can produce more nuanced results for Chinese aesthetics. English is fine for international styles.</div></details><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Best aspect ratio?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">9:16 for Douyin/TikTok. 16:9 for widescreen cinematic.</div></details><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Does Seedance support multi-step moves?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. Use 'then' to chain moves: 'Camera: slow dolly in, then 180-degree orbit.'</div></details><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">What style works best?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Anime (especially shonen), cinematic live-action, and urban aesthetics all perform well.</div></details></div>
